'''Horizon Adjust''' is a feature within VR mode, that allows a user to adjust the offset of their headset's positioning to remain upright, and facing forward.

== Overview ==
[[File:Horizonadjust1.webm|thumb|A demonstration of Horizon Adjust being used. ''(Click to view)'']]
Horizon Adjust is a VR comfort feature, lettings users be able to use VRChat easier while reclined or laying down. When setting Horizon Adjust, the viewing position of the user will make the user face forward, as if they were standing and looking forward.

The feature was released on August 5, 2022 with the [https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/vrchat-202222p2 2022.2.2p2] update. However, the feature was teased<ref>[https://hello.vrchat.com/blog/addressing-your-feedback "Addressing Your Feedback"] published to VRChat's Blog at ''[[hello.vrchat.com]]'', on July 27, 2022. Retrieved January 14, 2026.</ref> on July 27, 2022, and then released to [[Special:MyLanguage/Open Beta|Open Beta]] on July 29, 2022<ref>[https://ask.vrchat.com/t/developer-update-29-july-2022 "Developer Update - 29 July, 2022"] published to ''[[ask.vrchat.com]]'' on July 29, 2022. Retrieved January 14, 2026.</ref>.

Horizon Adjust can be found within the [[Special:MyLanguage/Settings|Settings]] tab within the [[Special:MyLanguage/Quick Menu|Quick Menu]], under ''Advanced Options'', then clicking ''Allow Horizon Adjust''.

===Warnings===
Horizon Adjust can cause extreme vertigo for users who are sensitive to motion sickness, or those who are not used to using virtual reality headsets, and VRChat recommends combining other comfort settings, such as Holoport<ref>[https://medium.com/@vrchat/introducing-holoport-locomotion-9ada3abec63 "Introducing Holoport Locomotion] published by ''[https://medium.com/@vrchat VRChat]'' to Medium on July 28, 2016.</ref>, tunneling, and comfort turning.

==Settings with Horizon Adjust==
* Horizon Adjust Snap - A toggle that, when enabled, snaps the user's viewing position along a grid
* Set Horizon Adjust - Enables Horizon Adjust; this button can be clicked again to update another offset
* Reset Horizon - Disables Horizon Adjust, and resets their HMD position back to normal
* Set Standing Height - Sets the user's avatar to stand up fully. This can be used if the user is crouched, or floating.

